1
00:00:00,703 --> 00:00:02,602
So it was you?

2
00:00:04,013 --> 00:00:06,206
Are you her boyfriend?

3
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:19,600
[Best Mistake 3]

4
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,800
Did I actually call him yesterday because of my drunk behavior?

5
00:00:21,822 --> 00:00:22,865
Not by chat?

6
00:00:22,865 --> 00:00:25,174
I was insane!

7
00:00:41,091 --> 00:00:44,143
I guess you remember me now.

8
00:00:46,513 --> 00:00:51,049
Kim Yeon Du, Ms. Junior.

9
00:00:53,578 --> 00:00:55,146
I'm screwed.

10
00:00:55,146 --> 00:00:58,665
Sociology is not such an easy field of study.

11
00:00:58,665 --> 00:01:02,570
Although we have students from Economics and Business Administration,

12
00:01:02,570 --> 00:01:05,564
Sociology is also related to Liberal Arts.

13
00:01:05,564 --> 00:01:09,120
Why did I drink so much? Why!

14
00:01:11,471 --> 00:01:14,124
It's no use crying over spilled milk.

15
00:01:14,124 --> 00:01:17,059
Let me patch it up right!

16
00:01:17,059 --> 00:01:19,529
[Fix this!]

17
00:01:19,529 --> 00:01:23,322
Why do I get the feeling that this happened to me before.

18
00:01:23,322 --> 00:01:26,093
Well, then this is it for today.

19
00:01:26,093 --> 00:01:27,779
Good work.

20
00:01:27,779 --> 00:01:30,600
Thank you.

21
00:01:40,751 --> 00:01:43,727
Senior! Senior Do Ye Seok!

22
00:01:46,133 --> 00:01:49,100
I'm sorry.

23
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:52,452
It's not like I was pretending it didn't happen.

24
00:01:52,452 --> 00:01:54,947
It's really not.

25
00:01:54,947 --> 00:01:58,351
I drank too much last night.

26
00:01:58,351 --> 00:02:02,537
I only remembered when I saw your shirt.

27
00:02:02,537 --> 00:02:04,541
Before that, I didn't remember anything—

28
00:02:04,566 --> 00:02:07,084
- It seemed you didn't.
- Pardon?

29
00:02:07,084 --> 00:02:08,887
You can be careful from now on.

30
00:02:08,887 --> 00:02:12,697
It's okay. Don't worry about it.

31
00:02:12,697 --> 00:02:15,251
I'm not okay.

32
00:02:15,911 --> 00:02:19,103
- What?
- I'll buy you lunch.

33
00:02:19,103 --> 00:02:22,091
I feel so sorry.

34
00:02:22,091 --> 00:02:26,351
Okay. Whatever.

35
00:02:26,351 --> 00:02:28,023
Then...

36
00:02:28,023 --> 00:02:31,458
Speaking of which, how about now?

37
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:34,302
Now?

38
00:02:34,302 --> 00:02:39,230
He looks like someone who would enjoy brunch at a café terrace.

39
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:52,923
We could've gone to a more expensive restaurant.

40
00:02:52,923 --> 00:02:54,558
You drank a lot last night.

41
00:02:54,558 --> 00:02:57,036
Oh, did you also drink a lot?

42
00:02:57,036 --> 00:02:59,144
- You.
- Pardon?

43
00:02:59,144 --> 00:03:01,705
You drank a lot.

44
00:03:01,705 --> 00:03:03,592
It's for your hangover.

45
00:03:03,592 --> 00:03:05,261
Oh...

46
00:03:05,261 --> 00:03:06,145
Sure.

47
00:03:06,145 --> 00:03:08,413
And you should cut back on drinking for a while.

48
00:03:08,413 --> 00:03:11,190
Pardon? Cut back?

49
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:14,251
You were calling your ex-boyfriend.

50
00:03:14,251 --> 00:03:16,362
Did he see that too?

51
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:18,572
This is so embarrassing.

52
00:03:21,601 --> 00:03:23,644
You saw that.

53
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:26,331
Okay, thank you.

54
00:03:26,355 --> 00:03:27,716
Senior.

55
00:03:27,716 --> 00:03:30,167
I'm speaking from experience.

56
00:03:30,167 --> 00:03:32,195
It doesn't work with alcohol.

57
00:03:32,195 --> 00:03:34,072
It only harms your body.

58
00:03:34,072 --> 00:03:36,075
You have other things to do as a freshman.

59
00:03:36,075 --> 00:03:40,876
Try doing something else like sports or having a hobby.

60
00:03:40,876 --> 00:03:43,330
I should.

61
00:03:44,930 --> 00:03:49,190
♫ Will I chance upon days ♫

62
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:52,080
♫ that are like illusions? ♫

63
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:54,667
And watch what you listen to.

64
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:58,395
When you listen to breakup songs at a time like this, it seems like it's all about you.

65
00:03:58,395 --> 00:04:00,630
It's not good.

66
00:04:02,065 --> 00:04:04,561
Okay, I will.

67
00:04:04,561 --> 00:04:06,210
Thank you, Senior.

68
00:04:06,210 --> 00:04:10,760
♫ Even at an unexpected time like this ♫

69
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:13,340
♫ If you were here, ♫

70
00:04:13,340 --> 00:04:16,670
♫ I would only have eyes for you ♫

71
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:20,830
♫ I will no longer be afraid ♫

72
00:04:20,830 --> 00:04:27,270
♫ I think I know quite a bit now ♫

73
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:31,390
What's with all the sad songs today?

74
00:04:31,390 --> 00:04:33,870
♫ Don't change ♫

75
00:04:38,043 --> 00:04:39,345
It's all burnt.

76
00:04:39,345 --> 00:04:41,296
Whatever, I'm not eating.

77
00:04:48,672 --> 00:04:52,200
Jeong Ji Seong must be in the middle of his lesson,

78
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:55,352
and Choi Seung Hyeon must be in training.

79
00:04:55,352 --> 00:04:57,605
As for Seo Ju Ho...

80
00:04:59,407 --> 00:05:02,000
I have no one to call at a time like this.

81
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:04,444
[At the café in front of school!]

82
00:05:04,444 --> 00:05:07,516
[Enjoying college life, Yeon Du?]
[Cute!]

83
00:05:07,516 --> 00:05:09,334
[So pretty, Yeon Du.]
[Our Squirtle.]

84
00:05:09,334 --> 00:05:12,502
I miss you, Kim Yeon Du.

85
00:05:18,885 --> 00:05:20,245
Damn it!

86
00:05:20,245 --> 00:05:21,963
Did she get the notification?

87
00:05:21,963 --> 00:05:24,581
What should I do?

88
00:05:24,581 --> 00:05:26,893
What do I mean, what should I do?

89
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,400
I pressed "like" because I liked the picture.

90
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,400
I don't care.

91
00:06:02,762 --> 00:06:04,371
That bastard?

92
00:06:04,371 --> 00:06:06,541
This tteokbokki is a bit spicy, but it tastes good, right?

93
00:06:06,541 --> 00:06:08,351
You're really bad at eating spicy food.

94
00:06:08,351 --> 00:06:10,928
No, you're worse.

95
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:13,430
Stop!

96
00:06:14,441 --> 00:06:17,417
Who said you could eat tteokbokki in the classroom?

97
00:06:17,417 --> 00:06:19,395
We're sorry, Mr. TA.

98
00:06:19,395 --> 00:06:20,406
What class are you in?

99
00:06:20,406 --> 00:06:23,683
I'm a BA major, class of 25.

100
00:06:23,683 --> 00:06:24,526
And you?

101
00:06:24,526 --> 00:06:26,169
I don't go to this school.

102
00:06:26,169 --> 00:06:28,763
So you're saying you're not even a student at our school

103
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:33,590
and you're eating tteokbokki in this sacred classroom?

104
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:36,813
Your school is pretty intense.

105
00:06:37,697 --> 00:06:39,506
I'm sorry.

106
00:06:39,506 --> 00:06:41,425
What?

107
00:06:41,425 --> 00:06:42,670
What?

108
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:47,882
Who does he think he is?

109
00:06:49,535 --> 00:06:51,260
That seat is empty!

110
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:55,489
I sat here yesterday, too.

111
00:06:55,489 --> 00:06:58,225
Did you come to the library yesterday too?

112
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:04,257
With whom?

113
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,568
A senior asked for my help with a project.

114
00:07:06,568 --> 00:07:07,536
A senior?

115
00:07:07,536 --> 00:07:10,771
He came back from the military this semester.

116
00:07:10,771 --> 00:07:13,483
So it's a guy?

117
00:07:13,483 --> 00:07:14,609
Hey!

118
00:07:14,609 --> 00:07:17,963
Why are you yelling?

119
00:07:17,963 --> 00:07:19,689
Sorry.

120
00:07:22,634 --> 00:07:23,701
Well!

121
00:07:23,701 --> 00:07:26,971
Why does he keep coming to someone else's school?

122
00:07:28,624 --> 00:07:30,942
Why are you at my school?

123
00:07:34,421 --> 00:07:40,147
I just wanted to see you.

124
00:07:41,445 --> 00:07:45,021
You coming here like this makes me uncomfortable.

125
00:07:45,021 --> 00:07:46,716
We broke up.

126
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:49,068
How about you?

127
00:07:49,068 --> 00:07:51,046
Why did you call yesterday?

128
00:07:51,046 --> 00:07:52,688
What?

129
00:07:53,373 --> 00:07:56,166
We broke up, and yet you called me.

130
00:07:57,919 --> 00:07:59,986
That...

131
00:07:59,986 --> 00:08:02,873
That was a mistake. I don't remember it well either.

132
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:05,643
A mistake...

133
00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:10,664
Why did we break up in the first place?

134
00:08:10,664 --> 00:08:11,474
What?

135
00:08:11,474 --> 00:08:15,476
I really can't figure out what went wrong.

136
00:08:15,476 --> 00:08:19,546
So tell me. Why did we break up?

137
00:08:20,316 --> 00:08:23,519
Should there be a special reason to break up?

138
00:08:23,519 --> 00:08:28,260
It's just that we fell out of love.

139
00:08:32,145 --> 00:08:34,046
You're lying.

140
00:08:34,814 --> 00:08:39,461
Anyway, I was glad.

141
00:08:39,461 --> 00:08:43,904
Although it was a mistake, I was glad you called me first.

142
00:08:44,966 --> 00:08:47,683
I'm off. Enjoy your lesson.

143
00:08:51,223 --> 00:08:53,641
What do you think you're doing? Report it this instant!

144
00:08:53,641 --> 00:08:55,627
Report to 112!

145
00:08:55,627 --> 00:08:57,153
Yeon Du!

146
00:08:57,153 --> 00:08:58,588
Kim Yeon Du!

147
00:08:58,588 --> 00:09:00,523
Yeon Du!

148
00:09:00,523 --> 00:09:03,390
You already broke up with him.

149
00:09:10,016 --> 00:09:12,667
Yes, Su Hyeon.

150
00:09:12,667 --> 00:09:14,319
Now?

151
00:09:22,528 --> 00:09:26,732
What's all this? You didn't say it was a blind date.

152
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:28,009
Sorry, Yeon Du.

153
00:09:28,009 --> 00:09:30,411
One of the girls didn't show up.

154
00:09:30,411 --> 00:09:32,013
I heard you broke up.

155
00:09:32,013 --> 00:09:33,698
Just have a good time.

156
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:35,407
Hmm? Please.

157
00:09:39,713 --> 00:09:42,898
When I was in high school, I dyed my hair.

158
00:09:42,898 --> 00:09:47,793
And I fell out of favor with the teachers.

159
00:09:47,793 --> 00:09:51,972
Hyeon Ho dyed his hair black because of me.

160
00:09:51,972 --> 00:09:53,626
What do you like?

161
00:09:53,626 --> 00:09:54,636
What?

162
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:57,254
I asked what you like?

163
00:09:57,254 --> 00:09:58,106
I like Hyeon Ho.

164
00:09:58,106 --> 00:10:01,184
I'm still thinking of him at a place like this.

165
00:10:01,184 --> 00:10:02,677
I'm insane!

166
00:10:02,677 --> 00:10:04,303
Ho, what?

167
00:10:04,303 --> 00:10:05,814
Oh... Um...

168
00:10:05,839 --> 00:10:08,515
Pumpkin potato. Pumpkin potato!

169
00:10:08,515 --> 00:10:11,276
I like pumpkin potato!

170
00:10:11,276 --> 00:10:12,703
Pumpkin potato?

171
00:10:12,703 --> 00:10:15,539
Oh, pumpkin potato. I really like it, too.

172
00:10:15,539 --> 00:10:17,934
Yes, that.

173
00:10:20,429 --> 00:10:21,633
[Hwayang University BA 18 Chat Room]
[Anyone up for a drink tonight?]

174
00:10:21,633 --> 00:10:22,824
[Hwayang University BA 18 Chat Room]
[Anyone up for a drink tonight?]

175
00:10:22,824 --> 00:10:24,914
[Are you all busy?]

176
00:10:24,914 --> 00:10:28,552
[Are you all busy?]

177
00:10:28,552 --> 00:10:30,900
They're so cold.

178
00:10:36,661 --> 00:10:39,221
They look like they're having fun.

179
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:44,908
Who's dating? I'm just having fun.

180
00:10:44,908 --> 00:10:46,796
She's a BA major at Hwayang University.

181
00:10:46,796 --> 00:10:49,406
Her name? What was it?

182
00:10:49,406 --> 00:10:52,451
She's a bit dumb.

183
00:10:52,451 --> 00:10:54,195
I told you.

184
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:57,838
She's quite naive so she's good to toy with.

185
00:11:01,127 --> 00:11:03,078
Aren't you bored? Do you want to go out?

186
00:11:03,078 --> 00:11:04,940
Oh? No... I...

187
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:06,641
Let's stop drinking and go out.

188
00:11:06,641 --> 00:11:09,010
I'll buy you ice cream.

189
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:11,419
Hold on, I...

190
00:11:16,934 --> 00:11:18,943
Who are you? Do you know me?

191
00:11:18,943 --> 00:11:22,354
Of course, you're garbage.

192
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:25,493
What's she saying?

193
00:11:25,493 --> 00:11:29,503
Hey. Just go home and sleep if you're drunk.

194
00:11:29,503 --> 00:11:31,315
Let's go.

195
00:11:31,315 --> 00:11:34,001
He's making it worse.

196
00:11:34,001 --> 00:11:35,570
I told you.

197
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:38,390
She's quite naive so she's good to toy with.

198
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:39,282
Yes.

199
00:11:39,307 --> 00:11:41,017
Hwayang University BA major Kim Yeon Du.

200
00:11:41,017 --> 00:11:43,220
She broke up with her boyfriend lately.

201
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:45,787
Some bastard toyed with her and dumped her.

202
00:11:45,787 --> 00:11:49,181
Hey. Who are you to talk so rudely?

203
00:11:49,181 --> 00:11:52,528
And who's toying with who?

204
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:56,950
Garbage doesn't realize they're garbage.

205
00:11:56,950 --> 00:11:58,676
So what should I do?

206
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:01,600
I help them realize it like this.

207
00:12:13,175 --> 00:12:15,676
Thank you for helping me.

208
00:12:15,676 --> 00:12:17,429
Not at all.

209
00:12:17,429 --> 00:12:19,564
Sorry about the blind date.

210
00:12:19,564 --> 00:12:22,642
You must've wanted to meet someone nice.

211
00:12:22,642 --> 00:12:24,102
No.

212
00:12:24,102 --> 00:12:26,104
My friend made me come.

213
00:12:26,104 --> 00:12:27,296
What?

214
00:12:27,296 --> 00:12:31,940
Actually, it's not been long since I broke up.

215
00:12:31,940 --> 00:12:35,980
I was feeling down and kept on thinking of him.

216
00:12:35,980 --> 00:12:38,900
So I just stayed.

217
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:40,876
That's a relief.

218
00:12:40,876 --> 00:12:45,170
I also came here to drink because of my ex-boyfriend.

219
00:12:46,024 --> 00:12:47,075
Really?

220
00:12:47,075 --> 00:12:49,535
It's been a while since we broke up,

221
00:12:49,535 --> 00:12:51,679
but it's hard to forget him.

222
00:12:51,679 --> 00:12:54,998
So I'm trying hard to get his heart back.

223
00:12:54,998 --> 00:12:57,234
But that's just me.

224
00:12:57,234 --> 00:12:59,761
Then... Was that why you took a leave of absence?

225
00:12:59,761 --> 00:13:02,706
How did you know I took a leave of absence?

226
00:13:02,706 --> 00:13:05,310
I saw you applying to return to school.

227
00:13:05,310 --> 00:13:08,562
Oh, at the Department Office?

228
00:13:08,562 --> 00:13:09,773
You're about right.

229
00:13:09,773 --> 00:13:12,708
I took a leave for an internship when we broke up.

230
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:16,819
When I came back, I was all alone.

231
00:13:16,819 --> 00:13:18,464
That's what happened.

232
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,716
So I'm wondering...

233
00:13:21,368 --> 00:13:22,961
Do you want to be friends?

234
00:13:22,961 --> 00:13:24,003
Pardon?

235
00:13:24,003 --> 00:13:27,064
I'm bored by myself.

236
00:13:27,064 --> 00:13:30,275
And a bit lonely.

237
00:13:30,275 --> 00:13:32,369
Let's be friends!

238
00:13:33,863 --> 00:13:37,515
Sure! Let's be friends.

239
00:13:37,515 --> 00:13:39,376
Cheers!

240
00:13:43,456 --> 00:13:45,916
Ugh, I'm not feeling so good.

241
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:48,977
Did I drink too much last night?

242
00:13:59,206 --> 00:14:00,498
Senior!

243
00:14:00,498 --> 00:14:05,350
It was buy one get one free. Do you want one?

244
00:14:05,350 --> 00:14:08,340
Oh, thank you.

245
00:14:18,591 --> 00:14:20,625
Thank you.

246
00:14:32,862 --> 00:14:34,807
What brand is it? It's really pretty.

247
00:14:34,807 --> 00:14:36,776
- She's so pretty.
- Even her bag is pretty.

248
00:14:36,776 --> 00:14:38,444
- Is that Jin Se Hui?
- You're right.

249
00:14:38,444 --> 00:14:39,386
Why is she here?

250
00:14:39,386 --> 00:14:41,399
She stabbed her boyfriend in the back, but how brazen is she to be here?

251
00:14:41,423 --> 00:14:44,570
I would be too ashamed to come back to school.

252
00:14:47,704 --> 00:14:49,122
Where are you headed to?

253
00:14:49,122 --> 00:14:51,830
I have a class...

254
00:14:58,114 --> 00:15:00,916
How have you been? Huh?

255
00:15:00,916 --> 00:15:02,735
Unnie Se Hui!

256
00:15:04,429 --> 00:15:05,913
Yeon Du.

257
00:15:05,913 --> 00:15:08,349
I didn't know you two knew each other.

258
00:15:08,349 --> 00:15:10,018
Oh, I know him from—

259
00:15:10,018 --> 00:15:11,576
You go ahead.

260
00:15:12,295 --> 00:15:13,862
Huh?

261
00:15:14,714 --> 00:15:16,974
Oh, you two must be friends.

262
00:15:16,974 --> 00:15:18,234
Yesterday, we—

263
00:15:18,234 --> 00:15:20,110
I said go.

264
00:15:24,866 --> 00:15:26,592
Okay.

265
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:39,819
Wait. Can we talk for a second, Ye Seok?

266
00:15:39,819 --> 00:15:41,998
I missed you.

267
00:15:43,826 --> 00:15:46,930
I wanted to say sorry in person.

268
00:15:53,544 --> 00:15:55,420
I'm sorry.

269
00:15:56,063 --> 00:15:59,099
I was too selfish back then.

270
00:15:59,099 --> 00:16:00,867
Selfish?

271
00:16:03,797 --> 00:16:06,241
I think the orange color may work better.

272
00:16:06,241 --> 00:16:09,001
The symbol of this company is orange.

273
00:16:09,001 --> 00:16:11,403
Oh, is that so?

274
00:16:11,403 --> 00:16:14,114
It is better to put this on top.

275
00:16:14,114 --> 00:16:16,357
Okay.

276
00:16:16,357 --> 00:16:19,644
